Returns the values of No Change, Change in Election, Newly Waived, Newly Elected, No Longer Eligible, or Change in Plan.  No Change will be returned if there was no change between current and previous elections.  Change in Election will be returned if there was a change in coverage or dependents between current and previous elections.  Newly Waived will be returned if the worker is newly eligible for the benefit coverage type and they waived all plans within the benefit coverage type.  Newly Elected will be returned if the worker is newly eligible for the benefit coverage type and they elected a plan within the benefit coverage type. The pay range for a position. It shows the minimum to maximum range. The numbers are represented in the currency and frequency of the employee's compensation grade profile, or compensation grade if no compensation grade profile exists.

The pay range 25th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 25th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/4) + Grade Profile Minimum.

The pay range 25th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 25th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/4) + Grade Profile Minimum.

The pay range 50th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 50th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/2) + Grade Profile Minimum.

The pay range 50th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 50th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/2) + Grade Profile Minimum.

The pay range 75th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 75th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  Grade Profile Maximum - ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/4).

The pay range 75th percentile for the employee's compensation grade profile.  If no compensation grade profile exists, the compensation grade is used to determine the pay range 75th percentile.  To determine the 25th percentile the following formula is used:  Grade Profile Maximum - ((Grade Profile Maximum - Grade Profile Minimum)/4).

Returns the total calculated cost to replace the worker based on ~workers~ position of hierarchy in organization, length of service, and if the worker is a manager. The cost to replace calculation for manager is: Salary + (Salary/hierarchy count) + (.02 * Salary * 12). For non-managers, the calculation is: Half Salary + (Salary/hierarchy count)+(.02 * Salary * 12). If the ~employees~ length of service is less than a year the calculation uses the length of service in months instead of 12.

If no member resource is specified on any task in the phase, then all workers who are members of the resource plan associated with the project are included.  Excludes workers who have logged time against the tasks in the phase, but is no longer assigned to those tasks.  Workers will not be returned for projects that do not have any project plan defined.

Excludes workers who have logged time against the tasks in the phase, but is no longer assigned to those tasks.  Workers will not be returned for projects that do not have any project plan defined.

Excludes workers who have logged time against the tasks in the phase, but is no longer assigned to those tasks.  Workers will not be returned for projects that do not have any project plan defined.
